sentences: Keri-Lynn Wilson (May 17, 1967) is a Canadian conductor of operatic and symphonic repertoire.
She also attended the Banff School of Music summer program.
During her student years at Juilliard, she first performed at Carnegie Hall's Weill Recital Hall in May 1989.

From 1994-1998, Wilson was the associate conductor of the Dallas Symphony Orchestra.
Wilson became chief conductor of the Slovenian Philharmonic Orchestra in 2013, becoming the first female chief conductor in the orchestra's history.
She held the post through the 2014–2015 season.
In 2020, she was nominated for an Opus Klassik 2020 Award as "Conductor of Year," in recognition of her work on the recording of Rossini's Sigismondo.
